main event: A witness observed a long red top and white tail object with blinking red lights in Spring Branch, Texas on May 9, 1966.
interesting points: The observer initially thought the object was a regular aircraft, The object descended at an angle before ascending back to normal speed, Investigation indicated it was likely an aircraft landing approach detected from a distance, The aircraft was a Cessna Skylane piloted by an attorney from Houston, The object was visible for approximately 2-3 minutes during the sighting.
sighted object: a long red top and white tail object with blinking red lights
